<br>
It was mentioned some time ago that VI never called these weapons 'epics' (players called them that) but officially they are 'particle weapons'.  So, the point to not have to improve these weapons starts out with its name - particle weapons are never meant to be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  the</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> best (beyond its respective expansion).<br>
<br>
Secondly, they were incredibly hard to get at the time Kunark came out.  I'm sure there are people that remember doing these fights during the Kunark expansions that wore Gauntlets of Fiery Might wielding SSoYs and remembered that they got their asses handed to them good; now these fights are trivial even for lesser guilds.  Why should 'trivial' content yield superior weapons?<br>
<br>
Third and finally, these weapons are actually still very high up on the list of 'uber' weapons.  Sure, their ratios aren't as good as they (then) seem to be but they do have much better stats/resists and great utility effects ... that's more than most weapons have even out of Luclin.  <br>
<br>
I wouldn't trade my Innoruuk's Curse for any 2hander out there except my primals (which I swap out for my epic anyways after it procs) right now.  The only weapons that I'd swap out my epic for are the 50+ damage weapons that came out of TOV/Luclin ubers ... but how many chances will I have to get that?  Plus, the effect on my epic is good enough that I'd probably use it over any weapon for soloing despite its inferior damage.<br>
<br>
So in the end, why improve the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  particle weapons</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in light of knowing that they are never meant to be improved, are of trivial content from 2 expansions ago, and yet <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  still</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> have great additional stats and effects over <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  most</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> weapons out there?<br>
<br>
Can't give people weapons that are better anything else out there for fighting mobs that can be killed with as little as four manaburn wizards or 2-groups. <p><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="400">
